history.content: Homeworks are not too difficult nor time consuming for this class, IF you've taken AP Physics in high school. However, the homeworks do not in any way represent what the exams are like. As such, you definitely want to keep up with the material and spend a decent amount of time doing extra practice problems do well on the exams.

(This is related to the natural science requirement) Still have to take the 7 series; anyone have any advice on doing well in the class? I've heard that it can be a pretty big work load. Looks like they haven't listed the professors for Fall 2017 yet on Calcentral. Any tips would be greatly appreciated! :)
